#PGML

BEGIN_PGML

[@ image( "21-S-4.9-RP-01.png", width=>[$width], height=>[$height]) @]*

A metal beam is fixed onto a wall and supports a distributed load. If [`w(x) = Cx^3`] and has a maximum value of [`[$w_max] \: \textrm{N/m}`] at the end of the beam, simplify the distributed load into an equivalent force. Find the magnitude of the equivalent force and the distance along the beam from [`A`], [`x_E`], where the equivalent force acts on. Let [`d = [$d] \: \textrm{m}`].


Find the value for [`C`].

[`C =`] [___]{"$C"} [`\: \textrm{N/m^4}`]


Find the magnitude of the equivalent force, [`F_E`], and the location on the beam where it acts [`x_E`].

[`F_E =`] [___]{"$F_E"} [`\: \textrm{N}`]

[`x_E =`] [___]{"$x_E"} [`\: \textrm{m}`]


END_PGML

